description.narrative: UNICEF contributed to the establishment of a national multisectoral technical committee for Early Childhood Development (ECD)/Care for Child Development (CCD), stimulating increased collaboration among sectors (Education, Health, Nutrition, Protection). A national roadmap for CCD was developed in line with the global framework. The MoH demonstrated commitment to revitalizing primary health care; this high-level engagement places primary health care as a front-runner entry point for multi-sectoral programme implementation, with increased equity and geographic convergence. The WASH sector focused on the development, validation and sharing of the roadmap "Free Senegal from open defecation by 2030". | Status:On-track | As-of Date:10/02/2020
